																		One Year
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227370" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1495134793 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 May 2017 19:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2825668">
									

<p>So it's been a year now since this was written. Man, a lot has happened since then. When I posted this, Third Law was still largely in the conceptual stages, and now it's the third largest canon on the site. Three Portlands, which began merely as a setting of convenience for this tale, is now an established setting with a hub and tags. The characters in this have been used by other authors, like Myra's appearance in Conwell's excellent <a href="/scp-3960">SCP-3960</a>. At +67, it's currently in the top 20% of tales on the site. I could not have predicted or expected anything like this when I first wrote this.</p>
<p>As it stands, this is among my favorite things I've written for the site, and there's very little I would do to change it. Writing this, and seeing the reaction to it, is what finally convinced me that I could write fiction (semi-)professionally. So, thank you everyone who read this, voted on it, left a comment, discussed it in chat, or wrote your own tales borrowing elements from this one. You're all awesome, and without you, I wouldn't be the writer I am today.</p>

							</div>

								
					
